The Boko Haram sect has allegedly committed the gruesome murder of innocent civilians. HumAngle reported Saturday night that the terrorists beheaded 43 farmers. The massacre occurred today in Zabarmari, less than 20 km from Maiduguri, the capital of Borno State. Corpses of the victims have arrived in Zabarmari village, Jere Local Government Area. Residents claim they are waiting for Governor Babagana Zulum to see the bodies and address them. When contacted, Director, Army Public Relations, Sagir Musa, directed DAILY POST to the Coordinator of Defence Media Operations, John Enenche. The military spokesman didnâ€™t take calls as at press time.